# The Core Pod Lifecycle

## The phases

```
Pending  → scheduled, pulling image, init containers
   ↓
Running  → ≥ 1 container up
   ↓
Succeeded (exit 0)   |   Failed (non-zero)
Unknown  → node lost contact with the api-server
```

## Living with a pod

- **`get pods`** — `-w` watch · `-o wide` node+IP · `-A` all namespaces
- **`describe pod`** — events, conditions, last restart reason. The *"why is it sad"* command.
- **`logs`** — `-f` follow · `--previous` the crashed instance
- **`exec -it <p> -- sh`** — a shell inside; `--` splits kubectl flags from your command
- **`port-forward <p> 8080:80`** — tunnel a local port before a Service exists
- **`delete pod`** — bare pod stays gone; **controller-owned → replaced in seconds**

## The lesson

> A **bare Pod is mortal**. A **controller-managed Pod is resurrected** — desired state wins.
